First, we identify the “quick assets” that are used to calculate the Quick Ratio. These include: 

• Cash on Hand  
• Bank Deposits  
• Interest Receivable  
• Accounts Receivable  

Note that Inventory is excluded.

Step 1: Sum the quick assets using the End_amount values:  
 Cash on Hand = 145666.48  
 Bank Deposits = 194711.58  
 Interest Receivable = 1731.44  
 Accounts Receivable = 3558301.64  

Total Quick Assets = 145666.48 + 194711.58 + 1731.44 + 3558301.64  
  = 3900411.14

Step 2: Identify the Total Current Liabilities (End_amount):  
 Total Current Liabilities = 3054996.05

Step 3: Calculate the Quick Ratio:  
 Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
  = 3900411.14 / 3054996.05  
  ≈ 1.28

Thus, the Quick Ratio at the end of the reporting period is approximately 1.28.
